docs.lead_paragraph: The party’s leadership sees an opening to derail Republicans who are facing re-election by blaming them for the delay in confirming Judge Merrick B. Garland.
docs.abstract: Democrats are trying to make Supreme Court nomination into significant election issue in light of fact that Donald Trump's floundering presidential campaign is dragging down chances Republicans will retain control of both chambers of Congress; Democratic Sen Harry Reid, minority leader, is threatening to stall legislative priorities of Republicans unless Judge Merrick B Garland's nomination to court is acted on.

headline.main: As Donald Trump Falters, Democrats Plan to Press Fight for Supreme Court
headline.print_headline: Democrats Use Brighter Prospects in Fight for Supreme Court Nominee

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. Manafort leaves nearly a week after a report about problems within the Republican nominee’s campaign helped precipitate a leadership shake-up.
docs.abstract: Donald Trump's campaign manager Paul Manafort resigns amid controversy over his business dealings with Russia-aligned leaders in Ukraine that allegedly involved millions of dollars in cash payments and secret lobbying efforts in United States; Manafort's exit comes as Trump tries to reboot his campaign following disastrous stretch in which he committed series of gaffes, and it remains to be seen who will step into Manafort’s role of chief strategist for final 11 weeks until Election Day.

headline.main: Paul Manafort Quits Donald Trump’s Campaign After a Tumultuous Run
headline.print_headline: Add Manafort to Casualties of Trump Bid
